messages.message:
Patch Set 1:

Can we keep *stable/ and  *.php ?

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> Can we keep *stable/ and  *.php ?

How do we know that *stable/ does not contain content that should be mirrored?

For the php files: you want to exclude them due to the high number of files (~7800, without taking into account any other exclude patterns), correct?

Patch Set 1:

> How do we know that *stable/ does not contain content that should be mirrored?

What is the definition of something that should be mirrored?

The biggest concern is a file inside a mirrored p2 repo that is accidentally excluded. By referencinf the directory, we minimize that risk.


> For the php files: you want to exclude them due to the high number of files (~7800, without taking into account any other exclude patterns), correct?

I want to exclude them because there is no need to mirror them, and that pattern (*.php*.*) has been excluded for years, from what I can tell.

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> > How do we know that *stable/ does not contain content that should be mirrored?
> 
> What is the definition of something that should be mirrored?
Content that is either big or accessed a lot and does not fall under exclusion rules like nightly, milestone, etc builds or should not be archived/deleted after a retention time.
 
> The biggest concern is a file inside a mirrored p2 repo that is accidentally excluded. By referencinf the directory, we minimize that risk.
"stable" sounds to me like release-worthy content that might get a reasonable amount of hits. I won't fight on this. My goal is to avoid more feedback loops for negligible gains (of saving a few MBs).
 
> > For the php files: you want to exclude them due to the high number of files (~7800, without taking into account any other exclude patterns), correct?
> 
> I want to exclude them because there is no need to mirror them, and that pattern (*.php*.*) has been excluded for years, from what I can tell.
You are right, that this pattern was in the exclude list here for a long time (added in https://git.eclipse.org/c/www.eclipse.org/eclipse.org-common.git/commit/?id=e958129215fdc69500295745ac2e3e469135aa27) back in June 2015. It has only been added to https://foundation.eclipse.org/r/plugins/gitiles/puppet/modules/+/a0cc75b6002702ebea1f3bc8ed5ea62c426dc3a9%5E%21/ recently (3 weeks ago) though.

Patch Set 2: Verified+1 Code-Review+2

I think this is a reasonable compromise, thanks.
Change has been successfully merged by Denis Roy
